Your fingers close around the warm scones and slip them into your bag with the ease of someone who’s done this before. One for now, one for later, and one just because. You’re already imagining the apricot filling when a shadow looms at the edge of your vision.

Ms. Greene’s voice cuts through the low hum of the fundraiser.

“I see you’ve developed quite the appreciation for my baking.”

You freeze. There’s no point pretending otherwise—she’s watching you with an expression of mild amusement, like a schoolteacher catching a student passing notes. She clasps her hands in front of her, tilting her head just slightly.

“I do hope you’ve left enough for the other guests.”
